children.subject: I had the same question for eecs students as well! Is there any paperwork that needs to be filled out prior to graduation?

history.content: As long as it says that you're graduating in Spring 2021 on your CalCentral page, then we know how to find you for the "commencement" prep. The College of Engineering will be reaching out to EECS students, and I'm not yet sure who will be handling CS students. Normally it's the department, but this year is a little abnormal. If you need to change your graduation term on your CalCentral page, each college has a form to do that, and any of the advisors, including me, can help you find them.

I saw on the Data 001 Piazza that they are posting detailed information about their upcoming commencement, and I wanted to inquire as to whether there were any steps that L&S CS students who are graduating at the end of this semester need to take. Or are we not required to fill out any forms or provide any information in order to "solidify" that we are graduating at the end of this semester, or as long as it says "Spring 2021" as our graduation term on Calcentral then everything is taken care of automatically? If there is a specific person I should reach out to about this, who would that be? Thanks so much!
history.subject: Do we need to take any steps in preparation for L&S CS Commencement?
